{
  "stem": "7598.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "On that visa is added the picture of my brother, because bearing the same name as my uncle, he sort of became my uncle's son, which would have made it much easier.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "All of my cousins-- presumably because we were girls and were too young and there was no need for it to be on it.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The reason they wanted his photograph is really a sort of a proof that he was their son and therefore was also Belgian.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Life in Nice was fairly pleasant for us children.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We went to school, which was run by brilliant academics from Poland and Germany, and this took place in the basement of an old hotel.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And, of course, the lectures we were given were fascinating, because the standard was [INAUDIBLE] university.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We didn't take exams or anything, but at least we had our little brains sharpened.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the weather was pleasant.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there were, at the beginning of 1942, not too many raids.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We stayed in a place called the Hotel Continental, which is a small hotel where we rented some rooms and a tiny kitchenette.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But it was also occupied by the Italian delegation.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And as we all know now, except for Mussolini, the Italians were really very good to the Jews and didn't like the system.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was suggested to my uncle one day that we all went to Italy, because the Italians were much nicer to us than the French.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We had all sorts of minor problems in Nice, not really minor, by which there was [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] somebody blackmailing us into having to pay more and more for food, for ration tickets, until one day my uncle had the courage to go to the police and denounce this man.",
      "word_count": 52
    }
  ],
